# 3. 相容れなかった夢

Emu: I'm at the main gate! Okay, good...! I should make it in time!
Emu: Still, Rui said he wanted to talk to all of us... What could this be about...?
Emu: No, I have to hurry...! I'm gonna be late if I keep stopping to think!
Emu: Morning, everyone!
Nene: Oh, Emu, there you are...!
Emu: Sorry I couldn't come sooner! So, what do you wanna talk to us about...?
Emu: Rui...?
Tsukasa: We're all here now, Rui.
Tsukasa: What is it you want to talk about that's putting such a serious look on your face? Mind telling us what's going on?
Rui: First, let's all take a seat.
Rui: This is going to take quite a bit of time.
Emu: Going freelance...?
Nene: Yeah... If we went independent, we could perform elsewhere while also continuing to do shows at the Wonder Stage...!
Tsukasa: Well done, Rui! I didn't know you'd come up with such an excellent idea!
Tsukasa: But I can't ignore the fact that you went to discuss this with Emu's brothers on your own. You should've been more forthcoming!
Nene: Look who's talking...
Rui: I apologize for keeping that from all of you...
Rui: But I didn't want to raise your hopes before actually seeing if this would be possible.
Nene: That makes sense... Well, it's great that they agreed to consider your idea.
Rui: Yes. Of course, gaining their full approval won't be easy since this idea directly affects the park's profitability...
Rui: At the same time, based on what I could sense from them, our chances aren't zero...
Tsukasa: Ah, that's wonderful!
Nene: Then, if things go well for us...!
Nene: Oh... Wait a second...
Nene: Where does that leave Emu...?
Tsukasa: Yes, you bring up a good point. Your dream is to keep this park a smile-filled place, right, Emu?
Tsukasa: Performing elsewhere means spending less time here. Staying with us may mean having to set your dream aside...
Emu: Yeah... So...
Emu: I'll stay here.
Nene: What...?
Tsukasa: You're saying...
Emu: Alright...! I'm gonna go ask them myself about you guys freelancing! I'll be like, “Pretty please!”
Emu: Oh, but that might be tough since Shosuke can be really stubborn...! Hmm... Wait, what if we bribed him with...?!
Rui: Emu...
Rui: You made your decision clear last time.
Rui: You don't plan on coming with us. You wish to protect this place...
Rui: However, with that in mind... Please allow me to ask you one last time.
Rui: Are you sure you don't want to join us?
Emu: ...!
Rui: Yes, becoming a freelancer means no longer being a member of the Wonder Stage's cast...
Rui: Thus, you choosing to go with us does mean spending less time at this park...
Rui: Which may make it difficult for you to fulfill your dream of protecting Phoenix Wonderland and keeping it filled with smiles.
Rui: It's perfectly natural for you to believe that...
Rui: But I see it a different way.
Rui: I believe your dream isn't bound to just this place.
Emu: What...?
Rui: Remember what you said when we talked about our dreams on that desert island?
Emu: Oh, me next! Me next! My dream's to make lots and lots of people smile like my grandpa used to say♪
Rui: You wish to make the masses smile just as your grandfather did.
Emu: I mean...
Emu: Yeah...
Emu: It'd be really wonderhoy if I could make everyone around the world smile like that.
Rui: If that's the case... If that's how you feel, you should be able to do the same with us.
Rui: Our collective goal is to make people around the world smile through our shows.
Rui: So...
Rui: You should join us, Emu.
Rui: Let's make the whole world smile.
Emu: Rui...
Emu: (Rui must've thought about this a whole lot...)
Emu: (About our dream... About my dream...)
Emu: (He wants all our dreams to come true. He wants us all to smile.)
Emu: (But...)
Emu: No.
Emu: I'm staying.
Rui: ...!
Emu: Because...
Emu: You guys are gonna make the entire world smile, right?
Nene: B-But...!
Nene: You won't be making your dream come true!
Nene: If making everyone around the world smile is your dream, you need to do it yourself!
Tsukasa: ...
Emu: Yeah, Nene, you're right...
Nene: Then...
Emu: But...
Emu: I want to protect this park.
Nene: ...
Emu: When people stopped coming to the Wonder Stage, I felt sad... Really sad...
Emu: Because it had always been a place that made everyone smile from ear to ear...
Nene: Emu...
Emu: I want to learn how to protect this place on my own.
Emu: I want to make sure this park keeps being a place that makes everyone smile forever and ever.
Emu: This place Grandpa loved so much...
Rui: (I see...)
Rui: (She seems very adamant...)
Emu: So, I'm really sorry...
Rui: No... You don't need to apologize.
Rui: I'm glad we had a chance to hear how you really feel, Emu...
Tsukasa: ...
Tsukasa: Emu, I...!
Emu: Don't look so sad, you guys...! You're all about to take a huge step towards achieving your dreams!
Emu: And I'll be rooting for you all the way!
Emu: So, good luck! Make your dreams come true, you guys!
Nene: ...
Nene: Isn't there anything we can do...?
Nene: What if we tried a different approach...?
Rui: Nene...
Nene: When you said that we should start freelancing, Rui, I honestly felt really happy...
Nene: If they give us the green light, we'll be able to grow as actors by performing elsewhere with other people...
Nene: And it felt like maybe we wouldn't have to go our separate ways like I thought, and we'd get to keep doing shows together...
Nene: All of us. Including Emu...
Nene: But...
Nene: Protecting Phoenix Wonderland is Emu's top priority...
Nene: Even after we start freelancing, we'll still get to do shows there. We'll still get to be with her.
Nene: But it'll mean us slowly drifting apart as we pursue our individual goals...
Rui: Right...
Rui: Things will likely change. We won't be able to put on shows together as we have been...
Rui: Which means... We won't really be a part of the same troupe. We'll essentially cease being Wonderlands×Showtime.
Rui: I was hoping that Emu would accept our offer and come with us...
Rui: But if she's this determined to stay, then...
Tsukasa: Right.
Tsukasa: We're out of options.
Tsukasa: If Emu does not wish to join us, then the three of us will just have to go on without her.
Nene: What...?
Nene: Wait, Tsukasa, just like that...? You're really okay with...?!
Nene: Oh...
Tsukasa: To think it would be this difficult...
Tsukasa: To “happily” go our separate ways...
Nene: Tsukasa...
Rui: A call...?
Rui: ...! It's Emu's brothers!
Tsukasa: What?!
Rui: Yes, this is Kamishiro. Yes. Yes...
Rui: ...which means you're allowing us to become freelancers, yes?
Rui: Thank you very much...
Rui: Understood... Then, I'll be there to discuss the specifics at a later date.
